[In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 3 cases and 2 deaths compared with yesterday's 24-hour period (3 to 4 May 2020) when there were 8 newly confirmed cases and 2 deaths. A total of 10 804 confirmed cases and 254 deaths were reported today (3 May 2020), up from 10 801 cases and 252 deaths yesterday (2 May 2020). The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 33 consecutive days and below 50 for 26 consecutive days. 16 of the 17 regions did not report any newly confirmed cases; all of the 3 newly confirmed cases were imported cases, including 2 newly confirmed cases in quarantine. While transmission hasn't been interrupted, the move to social distancing helped impact local transmission, so during the past 2 weeks, 71.7% of newly confirmed cases were importation related. As they move to the next phase "Distancing in Daily Life," all eyes will be on the country to see if they can maintain the level of control they have had.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7300349,195.- Mod.MPP]

