[The tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Italy is now 211 938 cases, including 29 079 deaths, up from 210 717 cases and 28 884 deaths reported on 3 May 2020. The 24-hour change between 3 and 4 May 2020 was 1221 newly confirmed cases, compared with 1389 newly confirmed cases between 2 and 3 May 2020. The numbers of hospitalized cases and cases in the ICU are also experiencing a decline.

Cases continue to be concentrated in the northern part of the country, in Lombardy, the epicenter of the outbreak, Emilia-Romagna, Veneto, and Piedmont. These 4 provinces combined account for 80.5% of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. Lombardy is the main contributor, representing 47.3% of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. In addition to Lombardy, Emilia-Romagna, and Piedmont are the only other provinces reporting more than 100 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. 3 provinces reported 0 newly confirmed cases, 1 province reported 2 fewer cases than yesterday (3 May 2020) 6 additional provinces reported less than 10 newly confirmed cases, and another 6 provinces reported less than 50 newly confirmed cases, all signs of decreasing local transmission.

There is an excellent interactive map at http://opendatadpc.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/b0c68bce2cce478eaac82fe38d4138b1 to visualize the caseloads per region in near real time.

On 9 Mar 2020, Italy announced a lockdown for the northern provinces, where the outbreak was concentrated. On 10 Mar 2020, this was expanded to be countrywide. On 11 Mar 2020, Italy announced the closure of non-essential businesses. It is now 38 days since the start of the lockdown in the north and 36 days since the countrywide lockdown. The lockdown was extended through, 3 May 2020 (see ProMED-mail post 20200411.7211958 for details). All eyes will be on Italy as lockdown restrictions are phased out. See section [7] below for details on phase 2 opening.

A map of Italy showing regions can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/italy/regions.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7300349,75. - Mod.MPP]

