[In the 24 hours from 3 to 4 May 2020, the total number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran grew from 97 424 to 98 647, an increase of 1223 compared with 976 newly confirmed cases reported yesterday (3 May 2020). The number of deaths has increased from 6203 to 6277, an increase of 74 deaths in the 24-hour period (as of 4 May 2020). In terms of total numbers of confirmed cases, Iran now ranks 10th globally, behind the USA, Spain, Italy, UK, France, Germany, Russia, Turkey, and Brazil. As with other countries that are lifting business closures, all eyes are on Iran now that "low risk" businesses are opening. The past 3 days have seen slight increases in newly confirmed cases from 802 to 976 to 1223.

A map of Iran showing provinces can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/iran/iran-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7300349,128. - Mod.MPP]

