[The above are the latest breakdowns of confirmed cases of SARS-CoV-2 infection in the USA, as per Worldometer data. The total number of confirmed cases in the USA and territories is now 1 212 835, including 69 921 deaths, an increase from 1 188 122 cases and 68 598 deaths in the past 24 hours. New York state, with 327 374 (27.0%) cumulative case reports and 3491 (14.1%) newly confirmed cases over the past 24 hours, is clearly the epicenter of the outbreak in the USA, although case reporting elsewhere is increasing. New York City had a cumulative total of 170 534 as of 1:00 PM on 4 May 2020, including 13 536 confirmed deaths and an additional 5373 probable deaths (https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/covid/covid-19-data.page).

Daily reported case counts are high in Illinois (2341 -- 9.5% of total), New Jersey (1907 -- 7.7%), California (1230 -- 5.0%), Texas (1034 -- 4.2%), Massachusetts (1000 -- 4.0%), Maryland (946 -- 3.8%), and Pennsylvania (874 -- 3.5%). In terms of cumulative case reports, New York is number one, followed by New Jersey, Massachusetts, Illinois, California, Pennsylvania, Michigan, Florida, Texas, and Connecticut.

Repeating from previous days, more sobering, if you treat each state as a country and insert them in descending cumulative case counts, New York state would be number 1 followed by Spain, Italy, UK, France, Germany, Russia, New Jersey, Turkey, and Brazil as number 10. Number 11 would be Iran, 12 China, 13 Massachusetts, 14 Illinois, 15 Canada, 16 California, 17 Pennsylvania, 18 Belgium, 19 Peru, and 20 India. 6 US states are in the top 20 in terms of cumulative case counts (concept from - Mod.LXL). Even more sobering is that New York City would be between the UK and France (it would be number 5).

The US military has confirmed 7434 cumulative cases, with 289 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours. The Veteran Affairs reported 9627 cumulative cases and 298 new cases today (4 May 2020). There have been 2340 cases reported from federal prisons (64 new cases in the past 24 hours) and 2373 cases reported from the Navajo Nation (0 newly reported cases in the past 24 hours). Puerto Rico has reported 1843 cases (35 new cases in the past 24 hours).

The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention website (https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/cases-updates/cases-in-us.html) has a growth curve and a table giving demographics (age and ethnicity) where known.

A map of the United States can be seen at http://www.mapsofworld.com/usa/ and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7300349,106. - Mod.MPP]

